Content:
I had a job interview once where the question was "find all descendants of a DOM node with a certain tag name, and return them in document order."  I thought for about 30 seconds, and then wrote up on the board:<p><pre><code>    element.getElementsByTagName(tagName);
</code></pre>
That was what he was looking for. ;-) Of course, then he had me do it out as if getElementsByTagName didn't exist.
